cording to Thy great mercy; and according to the multitude of Thy compassions blot out my transgression.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Wash me thoroughly from mine ini\-quity, and cleanse me from my sin.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  For I know mine i\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 niquity, and my sin is ever before me.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Against Thee only have I sinned and done this evil be\-fore Thee, that Thou mightest be jus\-tified in Thy words, and prevail when Thou art judged.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  For behold, I was conceived in iniquities, and in sins did my mothe\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 r bear me.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  For behold, Thou hast loved truth; the hidden and secret things of Thy wisdom hast Thou made manifest unto me.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Thou shalt sprinkle me with hyssop, and I shall be made clean; Thou shalt wash me, and I shall be made whiter than snow.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Thou sha\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 lt make me to hear joy and gladness; the bones that be hum\-bled, they shall rejoice.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Turn Thy face away from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Cast me not away from Thy presence, and take not Thy Holy Spirit from me.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Restore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, and with Thy governing Spirit establish me.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  I shall teach tran\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 sgressors Thy ways, and the ungodly shall turn back unto Thee.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Deliver me from blood\_guiltiness, O God, Thou God of my salvation; my tongue shall rejoice in Thy righteous\-ness.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  O Lord, Thou shalt open my lips, and my mouth shall declare Thy praise.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  F\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 or if Thou hadst desired sac\-rifice, I had given it; with whole\_burnt offerings Thou shalt not be pleased.
\par 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  A sacrifice unto God is a broken spirit; a heart that is broken and humbled God will not despise.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 , and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and whole\_burnt offerings.
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37  Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par 
\par 
